titleInfo.title: Photomontage of yachts, a bird, Americans at the Geneva conference, President Coolidge, men with model ships, and the Deaderick Street bridge. Nashville Banner, 1927 August 28.

mods.abstract: Photomontage of yachts in New York, an albino blue jay on Harding Road in Nashville, Americans who attended the Geneva conference, President Coolidge wearing a Sioux headdress, men with model ships, and the Deaderick Street bridge with water pouring off from a broken pipe. 16 x 21.5 in. Forms part of the Nashville Newspaper Rotogravure Digital Images Collection.

originInfo.publisher: Metropolitan Nashville/Davidson County Archives, Nashville Public Library
